// M0 milestone smoke-test source.
//
// The smallest hexa program the native pipeline can compile end-to-end:
// a `main` function that returns 0. Exit code 0 == success.
//
// Anything richer than this requires lexer/parser features the current
// stage0-bootstrapped compiler does not yet support. See tests/m0/run_m0.hexa
// for the harness that drives this through compiler/main.hexa.
fn main() -> i32 {
    return 0
}
